      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Early eugenicists insisted craniometry proved racial types were immutable, claiming smaller brain sizes strictly indicated lower cognitive potential and moral degeneration in non-white populations. They argued that early IQ tests measured inherent biological fate rather than environmental factors, using these flawed metrics to categorize entire groups as statistically destined for submissiveness or forced sterilization. This pseudo-scientific narrative was built on the delusion that mixing races would biologically corrupt the superior \"master race,\" justifying segregation and genetic engineering as moral duties. While their data was hotly contested and statistically worthless, they sold this fiction as absolute truth to justify centuries of systemic oppression. Ultimately, documenting their errors serves history best by exposing how easily prejudice can mimic scientific authority.",
